RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 1 5F All Weather Track CR: 67. Maiden Claiming Purse 36300. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 121 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHO'S THAT BABY was allowed to settle having one beat down the backstretch, took closer order between rivals three eighths from the line, rallied three wide at the quarter pole, loomed the threat in upper stretch, pounced to the lead inside the furlong marker and comfortably came home for the win. I'M TENACIOUS bumped the outside foe at the start, was unhurried trailing down the backside, continued to see the field on the turn, began to lengthen stride catching up to the pack at the quarter pole, swung out in the five path with momentum at the top of the lane and closed belatedly on the wrong lead to the wire getting up for second late. DIXIERIBSY chased with runners on either side in the two path around the turn, battled for the lead two wide a quarter from the prize, briefly poked his head in front on the fence turning for home, could not keep up to the winner with a furlong to go and faded in deep stretch losing the place share. I'M AWESOME prompted the pace three wide outside on the turn, bid for the lead three wide at the quarter pole, was no match for the top pair running between foes in upper stretch and faded at the furlong marker. CASBY nestled behind the pacesetter in the beginning, was hard ridden trying to keep pace on the rail with others making a move around the bend and levelled off in upper stretch. FEATHERWEIGHT bumped with inside foe at the break, stalked outside near the rear down the backstretch, made a brief run three wide three furlongs from home through to the three sixteenths marker biding up front in the four path, could nor find more in the lane and wilted with a sixteenth left to run. GOLDEN SPRING tracked between in the second flight in the early going, was roused three furlongs from the wire, offered little response and backed away through the field in midturn. GOINGTOARUBA broke outwards on the start, took command down the backside, continued up front on the rail through the turn, was engulfed by runners outside with a quarter to go, faltered on the fence in upper stretch and galloped to the wire.

(Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ONANDONANDON broke out at the start, travelled in mid-pack down the backside, took closer order to track four wide into the turn, angled inwards off a rival getting out at the quarter pole to be in the mix in upper stretch, strongly closed between foes at the furlong pole and was edging away for the win crossing the line. TAMANA had a good position tracking the contesting duo on the turn, loomed four wide appearing to get out some turning for home and ran on gamely to the wire but was outfinished by the winner in deep stretch. FEDALINE pressed the issue outside at the half, shadowed the frontrunner around the turn, pounced to the front two furlongs from home, was clinging onto the lead at the eighth pole and faded against the top two while not switching leads to the wire and finished a clear third in the end. TENPENNY NAIL settled in midfield in the three path between horses down the backside, was mildly checked at the nine sixteenths marker being shuffled back a touch, began to pick up runners three wide at the quarter pole and finished up willingly down the lane to close in for a minor share in the end. SWEET NOLA trailed the field running inside down the backstretch, made a mild run on the rail midway on the turn, angled in the two path between foes straightening out for the drive and could not get involved in the stretch run. TAYLORMOON stumbled on the break, recovered to dictate the pace at the half, maintained a slim advantage while pressed outside through the turn, was collared outside with a quarter left to run, battled inside until the furlong marker and yielded on the fence in the final seventy yards. MANITOULIN ISLAND stalked on the outside near the rear down the back straight, had no run around the bend losing ground to others, could see the field at the top of the stretch and did not find more in the drive to the finish line to be a factor. PICK A PENNY tracked on the rail down the backside, was nudged on the fence three furlongs from the wire, could not match strides with rivals on the turn and was empty for the stretch run.

ROLLING HILLS was checked when on heels behind a fellow runner on the fence at the seven sixteenths marker, could not regroup through the turn seeing the field and showed some late interest to pass a tired one down the stretch. BLUES POWER pressed the issue inside down the backstretch, could not go on with quickening rivals three furlongs from the wire, was shuffled back and retreated on the fence in mid -stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HATMAKER GIZMO stalked in the third flight on the rail down the backside, was patiently handled waiting behind runners at the half, improved smartly inside midway on the far turn, shifted outside off the tiring leaders at the quarter pole, looked for running room in the three path in upper stretch, found a seam bursting through in the two path with a furlong to go and was edging away for the win at the finish. BUCK'S FIZZ had a good spot tracking the engaging pair on the first turn under a tight rein, took closer order to prompt three wide outside three furlongs from the wire, seized control at the furlong marker and stubbornly battled to the end just missing out for the win while saving second crossing the line. MUCHO MAGNIFICO stalked with runners on each side in the third flight down the backside, was roused between horses three furlongs out matching strides with the eventual winner through the last bend, turning for home was in the hunt four wide but needed more late to threaten the top two in deep stretch. AWESOME ENTRY hopped at the start, trailed in the early stages of the race, came under a ride closing the gap to the field midway on the far turn, angled out widest in the six path swinging for home and found his best stride late, closing in to be a fringe player in the end. THEFRONTIERSMAN bumped outside rival on the break, settled on the fence early on having one beat, stalked near the rear five deep outside foes when the field bunched up at the half, kept pace four wide running around the final bend and showed some late energy in the four path running to the wire. THOR'S CAUSE bumped inside foe on the break, travelled in mid-pack on the rail in the first turn, was tucked in behind the top pair at the half, could not go on with others and was shuffled back at the three eighths pole and finished up evenly through the stretch passing some. FABELMAN stalked in the third flight three deep down the backside, was hard ridden three wide with three furlongs left to run, made little headway on the final turn, swung out to the five path for the drive but was no menace running down the lane. CAMAROSA under a snug hold, took this field into the first turn, continued setting the pace while hounded outside down the back straight, maintained a narrow advantage on the rail through the far turn, battled determinedly until the furlong marker, could not find another gear late and weakened at the sixteenth pole. NIGHT STRIKER pressed the issue on the outside in the early stages, bobbed heads up front in the two path between runners at the three furlong marker, was first of the contesting trio to give way at the quarter pole and faltered on the fence with an eighth to run.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROYAL HUDSON tracked the contesting duo inside down the backstretch in the second flight, crept closer to the embattled leaders at the three furlong marker, had his sights locked on the leader just outside in the two path straightening out for home, took command at the eighth pole and was resilient between foes late to prevail by a photo at the finish line. DUBAWI BULL was off slowly on the start, co-trailed on the inside down the back straight, progressed sharply on the fence at the half, shifted outside reaching for more ground three furlongs from home, closed in strongly on the leaders at the quarter pole, loomed the threat in the three path turning for home, was poised to go by, rider unfortunately dropped his inside left line dueling for the lead in deep stretch and could not get by at the wire. WHITING FIELD pressed the issue just outside in the early stages of the race, began to edge away for a clear lead midway on the far turn, could not sustain the run in upper stretch, faded on the inside at the eighth pole and held for a clear third in the end. OH PEANUTS travelled all alone in mid-pack in the third flight down the backside, was coaxed for more going after the leaders three furlongs out, offered little run on the far turn but finished with a little late interest to close in for a minor role right at the wire. COMPUTER HACKER had a narrow advantage inside on the first turn, dictated the pace while hounded outside down the backstretch, could not find more trying to maintain the lead in midturn, gave no response when urged and stopped on the fence in upper stretch. CANDID CANDACE stalked near the rear having a few beat entering the backstretch, was shuffled when stuck behind a rival to trail at the half mile pole, was taken up sharply at the seven sixteenths marker and cantered home crossing the finish. ADESSO was in a good position on the the outside watching the front pair duel down the backside, took an awkward step at the seven sixteenths marker, fell, dislodging the rider and was vanned off. CLARENCE B settled near the rear four wide on the first turn, began to improve outside runners in the three path down the backside, was steadied with runners on each side trying to avoid the fallen runner nearing the seven sixteenths pole, lost the rider and walked off. TRUE SHOT co-trailed on the outside down the backstretch, started to move in closer three wide outside rivals at the half, lost its rider trying to avoid a fallen rival nearing the seven sixteenths marker and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 8 7F All Weather Track CR: 69. Maiden Claiming Purse 36300. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $14,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HURRICANE GIZMO improved smartly on the fence running down the backside to sit behind the front pair at the half, waited to pounce inside running throughout the turn, angled just outside for the drive to the wire, was full of run between rivals with a furlong to go and gamely held on by a diminishing margin for the well timed stretch rally. GUNNAWIN travelled in mid-pack between foes at the half, began to rally when ridden for more at the three eighths marker, was in range of the leaders five wide at the top of the lane and was gaining steadily with each stride through the stretch but could just not get there in time for the win. LADY EVA emerged with the lead while hounded outside along the backstretch, continued up front with a slim advantage on the fence in upper stretch, was asking for the wire holding onto the lead at the eighth pole and faded late while saving third money at the finish line. SNOW LAKE stalked between runners in the four path down the backstretch, was urged four wide midpoint on the turn, began to pick up runners by the quarter pole, was floated out seven wide for the drive to the wire and ran on mildly down the lane for a minor share in the end. MUCHO MISSTIQUE was unhurried at the back five deep down the backside, could see the field making no progress around the bend, switched to the outside off runners for clear run at the furlong marker and finished with intent closing well at the wire. SWEEPING PASSION travelled in midfield at the half, was asked for more three furlongs from the wire, made little progress running around the turn and was one paced through the stretch. GAVEL GIRL was in a good spot watching the front pair travelling three wide on the outside down the back straight, began to take up the chase closing in on the frontrunner at the quarter pole, bid in the five path turning for home, began to shorten stride between horses with an eighth remaining and faltered in deep stretch. ALMONTE PRINCESS was on hold trailing down the backside, improved on the fence through the turn, was checked mildly inside with five sixteenths to go, made a mild rally on the rail in upper stretch and tired on the fence in the final sixteenth. DEFAMATION broke sharply leading this field down the chute, pressed on the outside along the backstretch, was scrubbed on but could not go on with the leader three furlongs out and backed away through the field at the quarter pole.
